('Grammar and Structure', 'Verb Form', 'takes effect', 'The new policy, including all its clauses, _________ immediately.', 'takes effect', 'take effect', 'are taking effect', 'have taken effect', 'Singular subject \"policy\" takes singular verb despite intervening phrase.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Verb Form', 'had verified', 'If auditors _________ the figures earlier, discrepancies would have been caught.', 'had verified', 'verified', 'verify', 'would verify', 'Past perfect in third conditional for unreal past situation.'),
('Grammar and Structure', 'Verb Form', 'endorse', 'Neither the board members nor the CEO _________ the merger plan.', 'endorse', 'endorses', 'is endorsing', 'are endorsing', 'Proximity rule: verb agrees with plural subject \"members\".'),
